Out of about 50 walk-able restaurants  from my apartment, Bibibop takes the cake as my favorite.  It follows the Chipotle/Qdoda/Cava model of "pay based on protein, then say yes/no to 10+ toppings."  Except it's less expensive and healthier than Chipotle, particularly if you choose a base of greens rather than rice..  My order is spicy chicken + yum yum sauce + korean red + variable toppings, but you don't have to follow this advice for Bibibop.to be good.  If you're the experimental type, note that without paying extra, you can ask for sides of all six sauces and then mix and match as you please.
Basically the Korean/asian version of Chipotle; build your bowl at the counter assembly-line style. Ingredients are tasty and fresh, a good choice for a quick meal.

This is my first time visiting this location. I wasn't too thrilled with the food, overall I felt as if it should have been better. I ordered a large bowl but was barely given any rice, the beef was very tough, and the servers were in a rush to complete my order. I probably won't visit this location again.

My friend and I enjoyed lunch here. We each had the people composing the food bowls start with the salad greens, add a scoop of purple rice, add spicy chicken chunks, add a variety of shredded veggies and top with a sauce. I chose the sesame ginger sauce. It made a very filling and tasty lunch, that I ate with the offered chopsticks. I also tried a bottle of the aloe drink, the version flavored with watermelon and peach - a new and enjoyable drink for me. A definite find, a place to which I plan to return often for an enjoyable quick meal.

Delicious healthy food and great customer service! But needs to improve the accuracy and clarity of the labeling of what is gluten free throughout the menus in the store. It is not clearly labeled that the chicken is gluten free. I was given chicken that has not been marinated, so it’s awesome to be able to eat organic gluten free chicken here. Also sesame ginger dressing is not consistently listed as being gluten free. Overall, excellent attempts on labeling the menus. Clear it up and offer gluten free chicken on the menu and I would give five stars!
